065年","1140":"1140年","ABT 1119":"大约1119年","1092":"1092年","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"法国布列塔尼普盧易奧","Sarre, Kent, England":"英国英格兰肯特薩","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"英国英格兰肯特哈坦","lifeSummary":"Rohaise Bannister是Robert Banastre的女儿，于1092年出生在英国英格兰肯特薩。她于大约1119年与Robert De Crèvecoeur结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。她去世于1140年在她的家乡享年48岁。"},"hr":{"1092–1140":"1092.–1140.","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110.–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128.","1128":"1128.","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110.","1065":"1065","1140":"1140.","ABT 1119":"oko 1119.","1092":"1092.","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Francuska","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"okolo 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Francie","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"omkring 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Frankrig","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"circa 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Frankrijk","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"about 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Brittany, France","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bannister","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from Old French <i>banaste</i>, <i>banastre</i> ‘covering for a cart or wagon; basket’, i.e. a large wicker container. In the 12th century a Norman family of this name had estates in Orne, Normandy, and in England. Ricardus <i>Banastre</i> appears in charters relating to the Earls of Chester <i>c.</i> 1120–29. With what sense the Norman surname was acquired is unknown. It can hardly have been occupational, contrary to Reaney's view that it denoted a basket maker. It is possible that many or even all of the later bearers of the surname were descended from this knightly family. However, several men with this surname in the 14th-century Poll Tax Returns are described as servants or agricultural laborers, while Ricardus <i>Banastr'</i>, recorded in 1381 was a butcher. It is conceivable that these men took their name from Middle English <i>banastre</i>, a borrowing of the French word, and that it referred to a basket or hamper they used in their work. Alternatively, they may have belonged to branches of the knightly family that had fallen in the social scale. The term denoting a stair rail is unconnected with this name; it was not used before the 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Banister","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Bannister  .","History: The naturalist John Banister (1650–92) was born in Gloucestershire, England, and came to VA in 1678."]}]},{"name":"Rohaise","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."],"variants":[{"name":"Roesia","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."]},{"name":"Rowse","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."]},{"name":"Roese","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."]},{"name":"Rous","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."]},{"name":"Rouse","meanings":["A baptismal name derived, like the surname Rous, Rouse, Rowse, from Old French rous, red; from Latin rufus."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Rohaise Bannister was born in 1092, in Sarre, Kent, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Robert Banastre. She married Robert De Crèvecoeur about 1119. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1140, in her hometown, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"umbes 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Sarre, Kent, England":"Sarre, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chatham, Medway, Kent, England":"Chatham, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1092–1140":"1092–1140","1090–1155":"1090–1155","1110–1145":"1110–1145","1065–1128":"1065–1128","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","1110":"1110","1065":"1065","1140":"1140","ABT 1119":"noin 1119","1092":"1092","Plouigneau, Brittany, France":"Plouigneau, Bretagne, Ranska","Sarre, Kent, England